<br>
In unrest you learned what pathing was. If you didn't you died.<br>
<br>
In unrest you learned aggro management. If you didn't your cleric died...then you did.<br>
<br>
In unrest you learned what a real train was, and what it could do to you... or you died.<br>
<br>
In unrest you learned that Corpse retrevial sucks, and sometimes the closest bind point is going to be at least 2 zones away.<br>
<br>
The levels hunting in unrest marked the real first differentiation between the classes... You learned what a paladin could and could not do... or you died.<br>
<br>
In unrest you learned that shooting a mob and running in a dungeon resulted in the mob taking an odd route back to you, gathering friends and killing people on the way...then you died.<br>
<br>
In unrest you learned what an intentional, and unintentional train is... Then you died.<br>
<br>
In unrest you learned how difficult it could be to get a res, and that sometimes you have to just &quot;eat&quot; exp loss...from dying.<br>
<br>
No easy Lake of Ill Omen.. no easy kunark/velios gear to make you fight like a pc 10 levels higher than you. Just the harsh cold reality that an adventurers life could sometimes be difficult and if you couldnt master those skills you had no business in Guk or Sol B...<br>
<br>
/nostalga off<br>
