<br>
Unrest is interesting.  Some areas are linked to each other.  The tower (where the hags are) and the bar (whether the undead barkeep is) are linked.  If you are in the tower, expect to get the bar up for a visit.  Back in the old days, the bar and tower areas were two-group affairs--you got one group to take the tower, and the other group to take the bar.  If the bar wasn't camped, you didn't take the tower because you'd be inviting a nasty fight.  Fighting on the stairs is bad.  You'll end up pulling MOBs from adjacent rooms.<br>
<br>
My level progression in Unrest was thus: Levels 19-20ish, round room on the first level plus the rest of the first level of the house.  Levels 20-24, the bar and the magi room; sometimes the Hand room.  24-26 the tower.  At 26, the basement was the place to be; the pit around 26-28.  At 28, you hit the bloodpool and the ghost room.  You can stay in the ghost room until around 35, but by then it's time to go to another dungeon like Sol B or Lower Guk.<br>
<br>
Good luck.<br>
<br>
